AI/ML (Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning)
 * TensorFlow: A comprehensive open-source platform for machine learning. It has a flexible ecosystem of tools, libraries, and community resources that lets researchers and developers build and deploy ML-powered applications.
 * PyTorch: An open-source machine learning library based on the Torch library, used for applications such as computer vision and natural language processing.
 * scikit-learn: A free software machine learning library for the Python programming language. It features various classification, regression and clustering algorithms including support vector machines, random forests, gradient boosting, k-means and DBSCAN, and is designed to interoperate with the Python numerical and scientific libraries NumPy and SciPy.
 * Keras: An open-source software library that provides a Python interface for artificial neural networks. Keras acts as an interface for the TensorFlow library.
LLM (Large Language Models) & NLP (Natural Language Processing)
 * Hugging Face Transformers: A library that provides thousands of pretrained models to perform tasks on different modalities such as text, vision, and audio.
 * NLTK (Natural Language Toolkit): A suite of libraries and programs for symbolic and statistical natural language processing for English written in the Python programming language.
 * spaCy: An open-source software library for advanced Natural Language Processing, written in Python and Cython.
 * Gensim: An open-source library for unsupervised topic modeling and natural language processing, using modern statistical machine learning.
3DPoD (3D Print on Demand) & PoD (Print on Demand)
 * 3DPrinterOS: A cloud-based platform for managing 3D printers and files. They offer APIs to integrate their services into your applications.
 * Prodigi: A global print-on-demand platform that offers an API to integrate their printing and dropshipping services.
 * Peecho: A print-on-demand company that provides a Print API to automate the process of printing and shipping products.
 * Print API: Another print-on-demand service with a REST API to integrate their services into your applications.
Voice
 * Mozilla DeepSpeech: An open-source Speech-to-Text engine that can run in real-time on a range of devices.
 * Kaldi: A toolkit for speech recognition written in C++ and licensed under the Apache License.
 * CMU Sphinx: A speaker-independent large vocabulary continuous speech recognizer released under a BSD style license.
 * Mozilla TTS: A library for Text-to-Speech synthesis that is based on deep learning.
 * eSpeak: A compact open source software speech synthesizer for English and other languages, for Linux and Windows.
